                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It is much easier to just consider N(x) = x - floor( sqrt(x)) which is equal to the number of non-squares less than or equal to x. Then it's trivial to check that N(44²) = 1936-44 < 1973 and N(45²) > 1973 so we seek x between 44² and 45² such that x - 44 = 1973. Thus, x = 2017."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

